# No Cursor / AI attribution in shipped content

In anything that may be **committed, published, or read outside this chat**, do **not**:

- Name or reference **Cursor**, **AI**, **LLM**, **ChatGPT**, **Copilot**, **assistant**, or similar.
- Say the work was “generated by”, “written with”, or “created using” those tools.

Applies to: **commit messages**, **README/docs**, **PR/issue descriptions**, **code comments**, **license headers**, **user-visible strings**, and similar.

Write as normal project documentation or human-authored prose. If the user explicitly asks for a meta note about tooling, follow their instruction.
